The paper discusses kernel $k$-means clustering, which is a popular machine learning technique used for clustering data points in a non-linear feature space. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of the Nystrom method, which is a numerical linear algebra technique used for approximating kernel matrices. This falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper uses the MNIST8M dataset, which is a large-scale image dataset, indicating the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical guarantees and analysis of the proposed method, indicating the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI).
